postcontent:
Have a beautiful little gun that I'm looking for trades on, won't see too many of these babies floating around.

.40 S&W, Chromed Barrel, steel construction, DA/SA and a VERY cool "tri-action" system.

The tri-action essentially allows for the hammer to be laid down for carry, but with a near-instant return to single-action upon trigger pressure. For an example, see this video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P89vfQUJVCQ

Very accurate little gun (I'm much more accurate with this than I am my M&P or Kahr), with an absolutely amazing trigger pull in single-action.

title: For Sale:  Carry Concealed Holster/Garment
postcontent:
Want to carry your EDC guns covertly? Have you seen the "Smart" Carry or Thunder-wear style holsters and wondered about them? Then noted the $50+ price tag? Pick up this one for substantially less. Note that the material in this product is light and is not bulky. But it will last for a long time in day to day carry of your  gun. I know at least four people carrying in one of these (even a fed,) and they've yet to wear-one-out. Additionally, it goes well with Dockers so if you happen to be adjusting things . . . well, it's not as conspicuous as those holsters made out of denim (unless of course you're wearing jeans ;-) 

You don't have to limit this to carrying your weapon. If you're traveling overseas to area where the laws are a little different and the pick pockets abound, this is a GREAT WAY to keep your ID, extra cash and credit cards from being stolen. Just step aside and refill your pocket/real wallet when needed. The spare pocket is a "premium" feature for the brand names, but this is always the way I make them. 

I have carried this way for several years now and can say you will not be MADE unless someone grabs you "there." Your wallet,/gun/spare magazine simply disappear. Can be used for full frame or small frame (medium and small work best) pistols. I have yet to see any wear marks: this style of cary is one of the best solutions yet. 

Why pay full freight to find out if you like this style of carry when you can do it for a better price. If you like it and want to pay their higher prices, well you'll know this style of carry works and can pass this holster to a friend. But, I bet this one serves you well for a long time and that you won't see the need to spend more. 

PS - I was very skeptical about this style of holster when I first saw one: afraid that it would not be safe. I have never heard of or experienced an ND or seen the trigger depressed after removing a weapon from these holsters. Additionally, I've tried pulling the trigger trough the cloth with no success. Add a layer of pants: I would guess it's impossible (YMMV.)

NO WEAPON COMES WITH THIS POSTING. THIS IS NOT A LISTING FOR A FIREARM OR OTHER WEAPON. BUYER ASSUMES FULL RESPONSIBILITY FOR KNOWING THE LAWS THAT GOVERN CONCEALING ARMS AND FOR THE SAFETY OF HIM/HERSELF AND THOSE NEARBY REGARDING THE USE OF THIS PRODUCT.
